content: Best game ever! I bought play pass specifically for this game alone, i had it on my old phone but lost the account so i HAD to play this on my majestic S21U display once again! No matter what i play i always come back to play this once more! I love every game that this developer makes, next up im gonna be addicted to holedown!
Got bored after 5 minutes.
Love the game, maybe having more "maps" would be even better
Fun game well made

Its an average game. It's a good idea, but just not for me. I find it very annoying that the workers are stupid. If I'm constructing something they take more supplies than needed and they lose the extra once completed.

Had it on psvita...constantly checked for it on Google play. Stumbled upon it just recently, and I couldn't be happier. Its the perfect mobile game. Well with the price. I promise. Five stars all day.
Pretty fun strategy resource game. I enjoy the dumbed down, simplistic look. But it is a blast!

IMPOSSIBLE TO WIN I would give this zero stars if I could. The minions aren't smart enough to prioritize tasks. So I have 5 minions busy doing something and 1 idle (asleep). I try to assign the idle minion, but instead 1 of the busy ones drops what they're doing and walks all the way across the station to do it. So I get attacked and all the minions are walking from one side to the other crossing in the middle and getting killed. Instead of defending from the room they were adjacent to.
LOVE IT, but not replayable after you beat it. Because repetitive

Very nice. The tetris piece approach is a bit annoying, but it works relatively well. The game is fun but hard enough. I do wish there was something you could get between games, for a sense of progress, but I guess this would go against the minimalist style.
Boring game with terrible controls
Awful UX
Very good game overall. Repetitive after a time. Would be improved with the ability to speed game play, but a very good overall game
What the hell is this? The tutorial makes the game unplayable! I don't have a clue as what I should be doing...

Super simple and fun, I just wish there was an endless mode where you can keep expanding and finding more materials. Or at least have a variety of different levels. I finished the game once and I feel like there's no reason to keep playing since it'll just be repetitive now

Fun game but gets boring around level 13 when I have all my resources and weapons up and running. I do like the last levels #26 to 28 when they come at you quick but it was so slow in-between 13 to 26 that I went to cook food while waiting. Maybe you can provide a speed up button in future upgrades?
Needs a samdbox
I love this game, it's difficult enough to be challenging, easy enough to pick up, it's so simple, the sound is beautiful, great game.
What an awful, confusing tutorial.
Unique and difficult to master
It's an amazing game and definitely worth a buy. I just wish it had more content or maps it's kind of dry.
Love it. First played it on the PS Vita & was stoked to see a version of it for Android OS.
Great game to chill, build a nice infrastructure, and pass the time. Be warned though, if you don't make good defenses everyone will die. There's a no enemies mode for just building.
It's a good lil challenging games
Weirdly deep, surprisingly addictive!
Quite challenging and fun, can get brutal in later waves.
Incredible game
Noice
Perfect!
Amazing. Played it on the PsVita. I couldn't believe it was on the Android market. Take my money!
RTS lite, very short.
Awesome game

Interesting idea, crude execution. TLDR: Its a 5min game stretched into a paid 45min format. - There are only 2 levels but they are effectively identical. - The AI is incredibly slow and the game has no way to modify the timescale. - The AI task management produces alot of redundancies, its normal to see half of your workers deliver the same resource to a building that only needs 1. This is very painful to watch when they move so slow. - There is little to no diversity in gameplay/strategy.
Content lacking
Honestly, with how good this game is, I am simply surprised at how long this took me to find it.
Great strategy game

Unbelievably amazing addicting zen mobile game. love the game play, graphics, and sound. this is the only mobile game that I keep coming back to consistently. New plus mode is fantastic, please make a sequel I will buy it!

It's a very well designed game, pretty fun but I think after 3-4 games there's nothing new to do and replayability suffers as a result. There's achievements which can contribute somewhat, as well as additional difficulties but the gameplay stays pretty much the same as when you first start playing
Thoughtful and relaxing
I've played it on 3 devices now, and have enjoyed every second
Sometimes the achievements don't work, but the game is so fun it's worth it.
Best game ever , great time killer!
One of my all time favourite mobile games. So beautiful and well designed.

The concept and realisation are good and enjoyable, but some things need improving. The first minutes of game are tedious, it's just soo sloooow. Any chances of adding an option to speed up the time? The other thing - I just died ca 22 wave because I accidentally deployed all my... kapsels? to research instead of defending. I realised that seconds too late and over 60 minutes of gameplay were lost. I realise that adding an option to save manually would spoil all the fun, but maybe doing something to make the interface clearer...?

Pathfinding seems non optimal and it's frustrating, units will walk from opposite ends of the map instead of closest target. Also construction has units attempting to work when the needed resources are already en route resulting in wasted effort, also frustrating.

I've played this game soo much, it's a good game worth the money i spent to 
buy it. Wow best game that hasn't been updated for 3 years. It's sad that 
they've discontinued the development of it.
Achievements do not work, but the game is fun.

Just brilliant. If love to see more missions, or procedurally generated 
levels, or something, but what's here is excellent.

There is only one map. Not even a random generator. Would be 5 stars 
otherwise. But at this price point I would have loved a refund.

I really like the twist with using tetrominos as the building blocks for a 
spaceship in a recorce management RTS, but you guys really have to work on 
the a.i. the little guys always do arbitrary things when constructing and 
fetching recorces like not realizing when another guy is already going to 
finish a project, so they just awkwardly stop for a second when they could 
have just easily predicted that they could have worked on something else 
further in advance which was very annoying, also i hate that i can't have 
multiple doors for a work room. Other then that though, the game is pretty 
interesting
Less IS more
Love how therapeutic and serene this is whilst elevating you appropriately
Fuuuuuuuuun harvesting and Tower Defending with a lot of replay value.

Really kickass game, got it for a long time! The other game by the same dev 
is also one of a kind and both with beautifull interfaces. Downside is I 
found a bug in Rymdskapsel after 45 mins of playing..

This game just updated itself even though I have auto-updates disabled. 
Very suspicious now
I had played it free when I first got a vita, then saw this $3.99 version years later and thought, " totally worth the nostalgia" still amazing to play as ever.
FTL except it isn't
Omg. the mechanics is so frustrating. It makes workers perform the most inefficient routes, MAKING YOU LOSE ALL THE TIME GAWD

Please please please sort out the host of a.i. problems. The way the workers move around, 3 going for the same one block etc, is very annoying+ pointless. Please fix. Great concept but needs lots of attention
Love it well worth the buy
Put it on family library
Elegant game, manages to develop great depth and replayability without requiring extraneous bells and whistles.

I love the robot voice introducing the game title, and the sound effects the minions make, except when they're getting hurt. :( This game is great for what it is, but would be incredibly superior if it had more to it. It is a one-level game, which is unfortunate. More monoliths, more rooms/functions, more enemies, more resources, more level arrangements, more soundtrack, more, more, more, more, more MOAR!!! This game should only be $1, but I am eager to see what the developer will do with my money, as I enjoy the direction this game seems to be going. I will be very unhappy if they do little improvement. >:(
A challenge, yet always a fun one.
I wish there was another level!!!

Rymdkapsel has garnered much praise for its simplicity, and it's a solid game while it lasts. But it doesn't last long. Once you've figured out the basics, there really just isn't anything else to it. It plays more like a demo than a full game. It's a good demo, no doubt, but there just isn't enough to come back to once you've achieved the grand total of 3 goals it has. *shrug*
I love the simple nature of this game.  I find it kind of hard to get started, but once you learn how to start, you conquer so much. This is a game that I would love to play again.
One of the hardest RTS games I've ever played. Simple, polished graphics, lovely soundtrack, easy to learn, and hard to master.

I don't know if it's the music, the simple presentation, or the gameplay itself that makes this game such a joy. I'm a big fan of RTS games, and this just nails the formula so elegantly; easy to learn, difficult to master.  10/10, would happily purchase again.
Great little game, but short. After about 3 hours, I'd done all the things.

Great game and concept when you start playing, but there's only 1 level, with 3 tasks to accomplish. Once you've done these tasks, (shouldn't take longer than 7-8 attempts at the game) there's nothing else to do! If there were more levels this would have been a 5 star rating. Great game, disappointing length for the asking price.
All i can say is Amazing and well done

Please add vibration when enemies are approaching, game is hard to pay without sound.  Also a big frustration is how dumb your AI minions are. They steal yellow triangles from your quarters. They also will start bring say many blue items to a construction site, even though it only requires one. They don't plan ahead, just blindly follow orders without any foresight for what a better path would be. Maybe this is intentional, but damn is it annoying.

I find it really relaxing to be in the world of this game, there is a great mood for sci-fi lovers to just be in space with this weird chill music. The game itself can be really hard until you get a hold of how to start your empire the right way.
Too unevenly paced and too short for its price. There is barely 30 minutes gameplay in this game, that is stretched out by an increasingly punishing second halve.
Really great!
Sandbox mode is boring, but that's true of almost every game. The "challenge" in the normal game is just facing more enemies with less time between waves. Just an OK game for me.
Neat game, but 1) not much to do 2) no updates for about two years  Had I realised that beforehand I wouldn't have bought it
Great gameplay, a little too shallow though.

Love this game! A pure strategic experience finally translated onto touch devices. The minimal art style allows for managerial clarity, and the shuffling tetris pieces provide an extra element to the gameplay, keeping it fresh. Only issues is that of longevity and late game complexity - otherwise, a beautiful title. Kudos!
Love this game! Took me 10 minutes to get into it but as soon as I did I found it hard to take a break lol loving it

A great game with a very simplistic design, plays incredibly well on my S4 I could see phones with smaller screens struggling.  The only thing stopping me giving it 5 stars is the fact that there are only 3 missions and I had them all finished on my second attempt. So replay value is low for the price mark.
Toooooo of short. One level.
Great game. Simple yet strategic. I look forward to updates that expand the game play.
Fantastic game
LOVED this game when I played it on my PS Vita and am enjoying the Android version just as much. THANK you so much for this game!!! Highly recommended.

I'm on an Android NookHD and I just bought this game, right? So then I go to play, and it keeps crashing upon opening. So I refund it then I reinstall, and it does the same thing. Now it won't let me refund, only uninstall and not get money back but be able to reinstall afterwards. Either give me my money back or plz help me fix problem saw NerdCubed play this on YT and it looks real fun
I'm sure I'd like it more if it worked on my device...
Add multiplayer! Let us send spy beacons to either attack or join forces to attack other space stations.

Artistic simplicity of the design and beautiful musical ambiance gives great background to its adictive macromanagement of a game. Build, expand and survive waves of enemies whilst branching paths to the monoliths! I really hope developers will expand upon the concept and deliver a sequel!
Smart, simple, perfect for the phone.
I keep coming back to it every couple months

Fossil fuels, materials, the purple resources, run out. Which is fine, but even in Zen mode, free style mode, once you have sucked up these resources you are essentially stuck. It's over, you can't do anything. It's not a challenge, its just time, a waste of time. It is not a creative game. Barely any interesting paths. On the flip side game is well made and has a good concept but was NOT thought through.
This game is great fun, quick enough for mobile with enough depth. Art style is also perfect.

Often the minion units will take multiples of the same resource when only one is needed so when the first arrives and completes the need for the item, it disappears from the second's, which must then turn around and get a new one. It's a big issue when attacks are frequent and resources are spread out.

Very quick to learn and will hook you! The core of the challenge is the limitations of the room shapes, which you can workaround by building and cancelling and is just too tempting to avoid. It does seem to violate the spirit of the game though. Maybe being able to swap the next brick but limiting cancel? Also reactors and gardens seem limited reason to make more than one or two early on. Garden/Kitchen/Quarters path finding seems buggy,  if they are spaced out the workers aren't efficient.

I found this game a really captivating experience. The initial achievements come pretty easily, but they rapidly get more difficult and really test the player. The comments about the lack of AI for the minions seem beside the point: this is the technology you have to work with, so figure it out!
lonelylonelylonelylonelylonelylonelylonelylonelylonely
OK. I love the graphics! They were full HD.    The different modes were cool as well. But maybe lower the price?
Very polished but has hige gameplay flaws.
It was quite fun for a while.
Fantastic game, although it gets a bit repetitive with time.
It's a very good strategy based game, and the graphics are absolutely beautiful yet simple. I love almost every aspect about it. I definitely recommend this game.
Great concept but not enough game modes, becomes boring fairly quickly.
Really well made game, although a bit lacking in content.
The game is too short, and too easy. On my third attempt I solved all 3 objectives. It was 2.5 hours of fun though. On the other hand it's the bomb.
Runs smoothly, works great, great game, but bloody hard XD

I was an avid player of the PC version of this game and think that the android adaptation is just as good. The simple graphics are part of the charm and the bad AI is what makes it challenging.

Was really enjoying this until I had played through in an hour, got the 3 achievements, and that was it.  Game over. Thanks for the $4. Add more content, at least a sandbox mode. Then 5 stars.
Not very fun. Premise of the game seems to be: Try build something, only to be interrupted constantly by attacks until everything you've built is destroyed. Was this meant to be a game?

The pathing/resource management of the minions are horrible! The minions tend to duplicate the resources they get all the time! You'll end up losing your mind on how stupid the minions move! I wish i could get a refund because of this.           The game also takes forever to finish and there is no way to speed up the game if you finish early and are just waiting for the waves.
Great little game, simple mechanics, and a nice example of what HaXe can do.
Creative take on the tower defense genre.

The core concept here is awesome. I'd love to see a sequel with a bit more longevity. It would be nice if the UI was a bit more minimal. Perhaps the costs for each room type could be omitted but appear onscreen as you drag one onto the map?

This is really a one level game. There are various Missions (you can't read beforehand) and you can change the damage between 2 Modes. That's it. I recommend expanding the game with maps that have obstacles and existing rooms to work around/with. Build gradually from just Extractors to levels that require everything here. Add Ground enemies. Add special rooms to maps as the center of a challenge. But I do understand it's $4. It's weird it got so many reviews, like NYTimes, for being so little.
Please add more content or level options. Would happily pay for more!
This is probably my favorite mobile RTS, its simple but challenging! I'd recommend it if you want a game where you need to manage your time and resources in order to survive.
Please have a sandbox in the next update
No sound or music in the game.

Really love this game, is one of my favourites on the store. The new modes have got me back into playing it again, & I haven't managed to complete all the objectives on the plus game mode yet, so is keeping me busy (: Great game man.
Idea of this game is amazing. Mechanics makes it so addictive. But... 3 modes make this game little to short.

A fun, addictive organizing strategy game. The map is always the same but the tetris shapes you get are different and pose a challenge. The Zen Mode (just build) is a great addition to game mode.  It does not have an incredible amount of replay value, but I see myself pulling out this app for years to come when I want a strategy game with little workers scurrying around. And there is the challenge of getting all monoliths studied without 45 minutes.
This game is so addictive and so simplistic in it's game play!
it is simple but very diverse
A stripped down (for all the right reasons) tower defense game that has a lot of humour hidden behind an elegant and simple interface.
One of my favourite games on andriod. Just need to add more stuff or possibly a sequel ;)
After seeing that there actually no glitches with the weird purple square farms it was a part of the game I decided to give it a 5 star this game is awesome I recommend itðŸ˜€
I can't even open it and I reinstalled it like 5 times.

Beautiful pure and simple game design, although still in need of a few refinements. The AI is infuriating at times. The workers need to be allowed to change destination during transit if their current destination becomes full and not all attempt to travel to the same place at once. Also, what is the point of the random room generation when they can simply be bypassed. Finally, its still needs an improved replayabilty feature, even though the recent updates have helped this. More modes please! How about multiplayer? Add a new weapons room type and battle real time against 2 or 3 players. That would take this game to the next level!
Nice but short
Challenging and fun
Great app.  I actually talked to the developer about something that was going wrong and he fixed it.  Great business
A bit short for that price
The game is basically 1 map and that's it. One star for idea and trance like music. Otherwise bad deal. I want the refund!

I keep dying in the later rounds because the game says my quarters are at full capacity even after several minions have died. So when I put the remaining minions on Food Service I can't replenish the lost minions.  Is that a bug or by design?
Worth every penny. As other reviewers say, very little replayability, but i prefer a good, well designed, not replayable game, than most of the crap out there.
It's too hard for my taste but I do like this game a lot. Its stars and good reviews are earned.
Loved the game and the minimalistic graphics. One of the few satisfying games for mobile.
Such a great minimalist RTS, with hours of gameplay specially since June 2015 update. Loved it !!
Maybe in a future update, you can have just a build mode and see how far/ big you can build with only a few enemies coming in seldomly? I think that would be very entertaining.
Fantastic strategy.
Thank you )

There are 2 modes to this game,  both of which take a bit over an hour and both of which will not present any additional challenge after your first attempt. There are some frustrating design decisions that make this true,  but it's a fun little game with a pleasant mechanic and art style if you want something to pay for 2 hours.
It was a ton of fun... For about 5 hours. I kept re-doing the same stuff. I just got really bored, really fast. The AI kinda stinks, and there needs to be a bunker or recall option
I reinstalled it but now I can't play please fix I use a nook hd works for most android games
I would love a "random map" mode with different monolith upgrades every time!

Love this game. Never left a review before and am doing so now in hopes that you guys see this and consider making more layouts. I would definitely pay for more. Beautiful design, and great simple but challenging gameplay.  I hope you consider making more visually minimal games, because I haven't seen anyone else out there so it so well.
Great game
Crashes on startup in the M Developer Preview
One of the best strategy games i have ever played

This is one of the best phone games I've played. The graphics are beautifully simple, the gameplay is engaging, and despite what others have said, I think there is some replay value.  My original review was 4 stars, but with the additional content, this is easily a five-star game.  Even without the new challenges and modes, I had no regrets about the $4 I spent.
Fun game that can be played constantly, especially since the new update. Yes workers could do with an update or two.

Good game but the AI of the construction workers need to be worked on, often multiple workers will bring the same material to do one room even though the room only needed one, they need to communicate with each other and be more efficient.
Now it's amazing. The replayability shot up a lot. Besides that, the game is one of the best android games, period.
Perfect game

The June 2015 update provides some much needed replayability to this satisfying, few-frills RTS. The random tetronimo room mechanic seems unnecesary since it can be bypassed by quick cancellation. There's no story; just a sense of loneliness and melancholy emphasized by the music. Who are these poor white peg people? Why are they in space and getting attacked by red ribbons? The finite supply of pink resource means they can't live forever. They cannot become a thriving civilization defending themselves indefinitely. Eventually, there will not be enough guns and they will all die.
Fantastic job, developers! I loved the game before, but love the game and its new update even more now! Keep up the good work!
Finally an update! !!! I knew if I held out long enough it would come
Just needs immersive full screen support
Updates are scarce. The game is a lot of fun, ''though.
1 Level! There's not even complex level design to this. Come on guy.
Elegant but limited
Wish it was longer with more scenarios.
Fun challenge even if the experience doesn't last that long.
I would have given 6 stars for this game if there were more levels for this money. Please, don't let us down, dev! Otherwise the game is simply gorgeous!!!
Love it
Nice concept and feel, but limited and gets repetitive.
Simply complex gaming.
Just downloaded this game again to play it a year later, I've already beaten it but the idea and artwork are so great I want to replay it.
Awesome game! Don't get mistaken by the description, it's "Zen" like BUT the aliens do not sleep. So get yourself a tea, a cozy place and of into space...

Rymdkapsel is fairly simple. What little the game offers is absolutely fantastic though. I just wish there was a bit more, perhaps some gameplay modifiers. Still, I'd say this game is worth its weight.
Awesome
One of my all time favourites but it's really lacking in terms of content and minion AI/path-finding.

It's educational if you're interested in design (especially game design) and minimalism; think of it as an experiment more than a licked mainstream game. If you're interested in short term entertainment to get 5mn wasted, skip it, this game will frustrate you by its slowness and absence of replayability.
It's short, but at $4 that's fine. An enjoyable little puzzle.

I don't normally rate a game down if it's too short, but this one really is. When you complete the 3 objectives in maybe the 3rd play through there is little point in continuing. It's a shame because adding a second level would have been very easy and I wanted to play more. The game leaves you wanting more because it is an interesting concept and very good looking, but it ends abruptly just after you start playing it. A real shame.
Meh
Great fun, time killer! Love it
Looks beautiful and is very challenging.
Amazing game, incredibly entertaining. Needs more levels so it can be replayed over and over otherwise it's perfect.
The gameplay took a lot of work. I can appreciate that as a game developer myself.
I really enjoyed playing. It crashes after all the monoliths are researched. Please develop more levels!
unfortunately too short !

When I first looked at it, I was skeptical. It was pretty expensive for a single game, but I tried it out and would recommend you do the same. The game isn't complicated at all and only takes about 5-10 mins to get the hang of it. It starts off invitingly easy, urging you to go out and expand. Then the game comes at you with wave after wave and it gets super difficult. It is a challenge no lie! I do agree with other people that one level is not enough, update with more maps please!

I really like this game, but there's something about the whole "getting attacked more and more frequently" thing that seriously detracts from the experience. You start out enjoying building an efficient space station, but, after several attacks, the joy is sucked right out of it when all you end up doing is rushing to fight off aliens every 30 seconds. As a game, I know there needs to be a challenge, and I don't have any better ideas...but it's just not as fun as it could be.
I loved the experience. The simple design and easy ui made it easy to fall in love with.
Shortish game but flawlessly executed!

Great design, the pace is perfect, the game is challenging but rarely anxious, and the concept feels extremely well executed. It's true, as other reviews have said, that once you've figured out the strategy the replay value is limited, but it is still a great buy for a few bucks. It's rare to find anything that as successful in achieving the goals it sets for itself as Rymdkapsel .
Fun for a bit, but gets kinda boring. Not nearly enough to do, and priced too high.
This games excellent. I picked it up because I had to have it on my mobile after playing it on pc. High replay value. Should only be a dollar though
Only complaint is that there are only three missions. If there were more it would be five stars.

Like the Trent Wolbe quote, I loved the game while I was playing the first level. Then when I beat the first level after a few hours of play I watched the credits and was shocked and dismayed that there was no level 2. There's no variation in the game so replaying that first level isn't fun after you succeed. With many more levels I would recommend this game, but I feel ripped off realizing it ends after the tutorial.
Really great game but there needs to be more levels/content for the price they're charging.
Addictive game for sure....I enjoyed this but it does have that sort of "never complete" Feel to it, which isnt it's fault either.
Enjoyable, but relatively short.
Glad I purchased this game!
YES
Best game ever. Just wish it was longer or with more levels or challenges. Super awesome.
Slick game, a streamlined simcity thing. Runs great on S3.
Nice game with very original 'workers'. As far as I can tell there is only one lvl, so that makes the game expensive for what you get...
Brilliant concept, loved the art, needs more levels.
Nice design, clean rules, but you probably won't play it more than once, because there are no more challenges. So nice game but definitely not worth the money.

Lots of fun for all the reasons others noted, but ultimately wish I had just opted for a free tower defense game for the following reasons: -Only one scenario. I only play games for a few minutes, and I like ending feeling like I finished up a level or got to a "stopping" point. With this game, you don't get that. It's just the same very long start-from-scratch game. Every. Single. Time. -HORRIBLE AI. Seriously. When you assign minions to new tasks by sliding them around (admittedly a very cool mechanic), the AI will often select a minion that is FARTHEST away. Also, they will often choose a very backwards route to get to their task, then finally arrive with the same material as another minion has already delivered and is no longer needed. Very frustrating. This is particularly troublesome in the later levels, when minions will often come out of the most critical defense stations to do a task you need alllllllll the other way on the other side of the board. Even after making efforts to create alternate pathways, it NEVER chooses anything close to the optimal. Ridiculous. Either let me select the minions, or make them more efficient.
Love the concept. Different maps and difficulty would be good though.
Amazing design and music!

A lot of people harp on this game not having that many objectives, which is true... However this game really feels similar to other resource strategy games, like Stronghold or Civilizations. Once the levels increase, the frequency of enemy attacks increase as well. There are finite resources, and the main objective is to last as long as you can. The unfortunate reality is that once you meet these objectives the replay value diminishes by a lot. The game writer could have made an engaging story mode...
I really enjoy this game
Needs more levels to be worth the money
Been playing since it was released on android.  Great zen survival strategy game.  Would love to see a sequel or additional levels/challenges added.
From start to finish an excellent and polished building/mining/tower defence game

Happy to pay - hopefully encourage more games for mobile devices that actually have a bit of gameplay behind them.  Will freeze up once you complete the level.  If you go into application manager and clear data you can at least play the level over again.
fresh combination, nice and very effective user interface, well balanced. imagine this: space invaders + sim city + tetris + tower defense + the settlers + ftl
Sorry. One level for 5 bucks isn't going to get you good reviews
The gameplay is engaging, but ultimately too simple. It's too easy for any replay value!
Expensive for 1 level
Incredibly easy platform to add new levels and yet the devs show no sign of doing so.
Excellent
It'd be nice if once a production area was full, it would empty out into emergency rations
I really really enjoy the game, but the brevity of it makes it difficult to recommend anyone. Wish it could be expanded.
Best android game so far.
The first 50 minutes or so are fun and challenging, but the difficulty ramps up like crazy. Kinda drains the fun out of the whole experience.
Game because it has building and fighting
So simplistic, but addicting

I saw the nerd cubed review for the PC version of this game on YouTube. Was hesitant to purchase but glad I did. Even though it's "one level", I've played and replayed it so many times that I've definitely gotten my moneys worth out of it. No cash shop, no timers, just a finely crafted game with tons of love squished in.

Love this game.  It makes you think, it gets more difficult as you progress and the music is really cool.  Not sure where all the hate is coming from in the other reviews.  $4 is about the same as a cup of coffee... I can't figure out how someone can complain about paying it for a game that stays interesting far longer than the coffee? Enjoy the game!  I'm reinstalling it on my new phone just so I can go back to playing.
Great, but somewhat overpriced.
Simple and fun game.
Love this game but very short. Please add more levels and a possibility to save.

This game simply is the best mix of tower defense, strategic construction, and minimalist design I have seen in any game, whether on mobile, PC, or console. The explorative nature of the game is intriguing and captures your attention, while the Tetris-like grid provides a dynamic challenge that develops a rigorous gameplay that requires specific planning and attention to detail.   Furthermore, despite the game's rather simplistic nature, genius design behind the scenes from the developers has created a demanding yet thrilling plot as one attempts to a successful ecosystem.

Great start but the tutorial completely stopped on me since I did something out of turn (built a Garden before prompted.)  Also, the AI is a bit stupid, its actually hard to work with.. they will pick up excess resources and backtrack if one of them finished filling it, which slows down the process more than it needs to be.  If that's intentional, it's a bit silly, my guess is it simply wasn't factored in.  Edit:  Had to update to reflect the reliable force close on losing :(  Crashes once the screen starts to rotate.  Also, sometime the pinch to zoom functionality stops working, and a couple times my game fast forwarded without any control and I would lose an entire game due to it.  Fun when it works but quite unreliable for a $4 title - beware!  Second edit:  It also force closes on victory - I researched all the monoliths, and instead of giving me a chance to keep playing and hold out against waves, it force closes and kicks me back about 5 minutes, which puts me in an endless loop :(  Hope these issues get resolved!
